
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ANALYSIS PHASE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

From the directory containing this INSTALL file:

    $ perl configure.pl

    configuring msvtools, version 0.0.1
    checking prerequisites ......
    generating msvtools program target
    done
    created msvtools program target:
      /path/to/msvtools-0.0.1/msvtools

Then, if you will train cell line models using the 'bam' method, run:

    $ Rscript install-r-package.R

Perform a quick check for appropriate installation by calling msvtools with
no commands or options:
 
    $ ./msvtools

    msvtools version 0.0.1
    applications for exploring microarray data for structural variants
    usage:	msvtools <command> [options ...]
    use 'msvtools --help' or 'msvtools <command> --help' for extended help

In most cases you will want to add ‘/path/to/msvtools-<#.#.#>’ to  
your system PATH variable so that it is available to you from any directory 
by simply typing msvtools.  

Familiarize yourself with msvtools as follows:

    $ msvtools --help
    $ cat README
    

